 {"id":"bd-mhu7","title":"Add ffs-fuse write-path operation tests (write/mkdir/rmdir/rename)","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-25T20:32:29.338695188Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-25T20:55:05.020860146Z","closed_at":"2026-02-25T20:55:05.020837012Z","close_reason":"Added/extened ffs-harness FUSE write-path E2E tests for write/mkdir/rmdir/rename edge cases; validated via rch check/clippy/test","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
 {"id":"bd-mzct","title":"Add unit tests for Ext4Superblock query methods in ffs-ondisk","description":"The ffs-ondisk ext4.rs module has 206 tests but several Ext4Superblock query methods are tested only through the ffs-ext4 facade. Add direct unit tests in ffs-ondisk/src/ext4.rs for: parse_from_image, has_compat/has_incompat/has_ro_compat, is_64bit, group_desc_size, groups_count, has_metadata_csum, csum_seed, validate_checksum, validate_geometry, validate_v1, feature_diagnostics_v1, group_desc_offset, inode_table_offset, locate_inode, inode_device_offset. These tests complement the facade tests already added in ffs-ext4.","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-02-26T03:23:28.818125035Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-02-26T03:35:03.599721597Z","closed_at":"2026-02-26T03:35:03.599691791Z","close_reason":"Added 25 unit tests for Ext4Superblock query methods in ffs-ondisk/src/ext4.rs: has_compat, has_incompat, has_ro_compat, is_64bit, group_desc_size, groups_count, has_metadata_csum, csum_seed, validate_checksum, group_desc_offset, inode_table_offset, parse_from_image. All 293 tests pass, clippy clean, fmt clean.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["ondisk","quality","tests"]}
 {"id":"bd-nzv3","title":"Close remaining post-V1 filesystem parity gaps","description":"Umbrella parity epic for the remaining major known gaps: ext4 casefold, ext4 fscrypt, ext4 fast commit replay, btrfs multi-device/RAID, btrfs send/receive, btrfs tree-log replay, and the remaining flaky btrfs log-contract tests. This epic should remain open until every child bead is closed, canonical docs/specs are updated, and the remaining gaps list in public docs is either removed or reduced to newly explicit blockers.","acceptance_criteria":"Every child bead has explicit dependencies and closure criteria. The epic closes only after all child beads close, docs/spec/parity text is synchronized, and full regression gates are defined for the completed feature set.","notes":"Planning rules: no hidden scope cuts, no silent partial support, and no feature considered complete without unit tests, crate-level integration/conformance coverage, e2e script coverage where the workflow is user-visible, and structured logging/diagnostics for failure modes.","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"epic","created_at":"2026-03-23T01:05:42.299075363Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-23T06:08:45.190920583Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["btrfs","ext4","parity","roadmap"]}
-{"id":"bd-nzv3.1","title":"Close bd-w3pv and sync ZERO_RANGE parity state","description":"Closure bead for the already-implemented btrfs ZERO_RANGE work. This bead exists to get the workspace back to a truthful baseline before larger parity work proceeds: unblock unrelated gate failures, confirm the targeted tests still pass, then close bd-w3pv and synchronize backlog/mail state.","acceptance_criteria":"Depends on the gate-fixer beads plus the existing bd-w3pv implementation. Closure requires: targeted ZERO_RANGE tests green, workspace check/clippy/fmt path green or any residual blockers explicitly tracked, bd-w3pv closed with rationale, and a mail update posted to the bd-w3pv thread.","notes":"Do not change feature scope here. This bead is about finishing already-landed work cleanly so the parity program starts from a trustworthy baseline.","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-23T01:06:12.160929114Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-23T06:11:19.395281172Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["btrfs","fallocate","parity"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-nzv3.1","depends_on_id":"bd-nzv3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-23T01:06:12.160929114Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-nzv3.1","depends_on_id":"bd-nzv3.1.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-23T06:11:18.319686963Z","created_by":"PearlFox","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-nzv3.1","depends_on_id":"bd-nzv3.1.2","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-23T06:11:19.394046956Z","created_by":"PearlFox","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-nzv3.1","depends_on_id":"bd-w3pv","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-23T06:11:17.181590411Z","created_by":"PearlFox","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
-{"id":"bd-nzv3.1.1","title":"Fix ffs-alloc batch_alloc bench for FsGeometry::first_inode","description":"Workspace gates are currently blocked because crates/ffs-alloc/benches/batch_alloc.rs still constructs FsGeometry without first_inode. Repair the benchmark fixture so benches compile again and the benchmark remains semantically valid.","acceptance_criteria":"Closure requires the bench initializer to match current FsGeometry invariants, an explanation for the chosen first_inode value, and remote cargo check/clippy confirmation that this blocker is gone.","notes":"This is a gate-restoration bead, not a benchmark redesign. Keep the behavior and measurement intent unchanged unless the current setup is provably invalid.","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-03-23T01:07:12.096831476Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-23T06:10:59.585763322Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["bench","ffs-alloc","gates"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-nzv3.1.1","depends_on_id":"bd-nzv3.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-23T01:07:12.096831476Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
-{"id":"bd-nzv3.1.2","title":"Resolve ffs-journal clippy too_many_lines on commit_transaction","description":"Workspace clippy -D warnings is blocked by crates/ffs-journal/src/lib.rs:commit_transaction exceeding the pedantic too_many_lines threshold. Refactor the function into clearer units or use a narrow allow only if the final structure is genuinely more understandable and maintainable.","acceptance_criteria":"Closure requires a defensible decomposition, no behavior change to transaction semantics, and remote cargo clippy confirmation that the warning is eliminated without introducing new lint regressions.","notes":"If helper extraction changes invariants or error flow, those invariants must be documented in the bead thread before closure.","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-03-23T01:07:12.265304882Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-23T06:11:00.621768377Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["clippy","ffs-journal","gates"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-nzv3.1.2","depends_on_id":"bd-nzv3.1","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-23T01:07:12.265304882Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
-{"id":"bd-nzv3.10","title":"ext4 fast commit replay: fixtures, crash recovery coverage, and e2e validation","description":"Prove fast-commit replay works under real crash-style scenarios by adding dedicated fixtures, crash/replay tests, and user-visible end-to-end validation scripts with detailed logging and replay assertions.","acceptance_criteria":"Closure requires: fixture corpus for multiple replay scenarios, regression tests for corrupt/partial records, e2e coverage with clear logs showing replay vs fallback, and parity/docs updates that quantify the covered scenarios.","notes":"This bead is not optional polish. Without it, fast-commit support is unproven and should not be called complete.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-23T01:06:21.322906659Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-23T06:11:26.018612914Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["ext4","fast-commit","tests"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-nzv3.10","depends_on_id":"bd-nzv3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-23T01:06:21.322906659Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-nzv3.10","depends_on_id":"bd-nzv3.9","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-23T06:11:26.017679076Z","created_by":"PearlFox","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
-{"id":"bd-nzv3.11","title":"btrfs multi-device RAID: supported profile matrix and architectural design","description":"Define the first supported multi-device btrfs surface in enough detail to implement it safely: profile matrix, superblock/device discovery flow, chunk and stripe mapping model, degraded-mode policy, and interactions with block/core/repair layers.","acceptance_criteria":"Closure requires: explicit supported profiles, explicit unsupported profiles, device-failure assumptions, touch points across crates, and spec/parity text that makes the initial support boundary measurable instead of aspirational.","notes":"Also define the verification matrix: healthy mount, missing-device mount behavior, read-path mapping, write-path constraints if any, and the logging fields needed to explain device/chunk decisions.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-23T01:06:22.365316340Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-23T06:11:02.942846688Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["btrfs","multidevice","raid","spec"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-nzv3.11","depends_on_id":"bd-nzv3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-23T01:06:22.365316340Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
-{"id":"bd-nzv3.12","title":"btrfs multi-device RAID: implement device discovery and chunk mapping core","description":"Implement the foundational multi-device support selected in bd-nzv3.11: device set discovery, chunk-tree interpretation, logical-to-physical mapping, and the minimum mount/read/write plumbing needed for the chosen profile set.","acceptance_criteria":"Closure requires: deterministic core mapping tests, integration tests spanning at least healthy and degraded configurations within the supported matrix, and explicit diagnostics for unsupported or unsafe profile/device states.","notes":"Keep unsupported profiles loud. The system should refuse or degrade explicitly rather than guessing.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-03-23T01:06:23.428684215Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-23T06:11:27.886602721Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["btrfs","implementation","multidevice","raid"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-nzv3.12","depends_on_id":"bd-nzv3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-23T01:06:23.428684215Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-nzv3.12","depends_on_id":"bd-nzv3.11","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-23T06:11:27.885763973Z","created_by":"PearlFox","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
-{"id":"bd-nzv3.13","title":"btrfs multi-device RAID: redundancy tests, repair interplay, and e2e diagnostics","description":"Turn the multi-device core into a user-trustworthy feature by adding deterministic redundancy tests, repair/scrub interaction coverage, and end-to-end scripts with detailed logs for healthy, degraded, and rejected-profile scenarios.","acceptance_criteria":"Closure requires: fixture-backed multi-device scenarios, repair/scrub assertions where relevant, at least one e2e script with rich logging, and docs/parity updates that state exactly which RAID/device modes are covered.","notes":"This bead owns the user-facing proof that multi-device support is real and diagnosable.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-23T01:06:24.487009536Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-23T06:11:29.008807717Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["btrfs","multidevice","raid","tests"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-nzv3.13","depends_on_id":"bd-nzv3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-23T01:06:24.487009536Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-nzv3.13","depends_on_id":"bd-nzv3.12","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-23T06:11:29.007893166Z","created_by":"PearlFox","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
-{"id":"bd-nzv3.14","title":"btrfs send/receive: extract protocol model and supported workflow contract","description":"Define the send/receive surface precisely: stream record model, ordering rules, snapshot assumptions, xattr/metadata coverage, error handling, and the minimum viable user workflow that FrankenFS will support first.","acceptance_criteria":"Closure requires: implementation-ready protocol model, explicit first-version scope boundaries, crate/module ownership plan, and spec/parity updates that describe the supported workflow without hand-waving.","notes":"Also enumerate the verification plan: send-only stream correctness, receive apply correctness, roundtrip expectations, rejected record classes, and logging/CLI diagnostics.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-23T01:06:25.619924719Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-23T06:11:03.378266802Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["btrfs","send-receive","spec"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-nzv3.14","depends_on_id":"bd-nzv3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-23T01:06:25.619924719Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
-{"id":"bd-nzv3.15","title":"btrfs send/receive: implement deterministic send stream export","description":"Implement the scoped send side from bd-nzv3.14 so supported snapshots can be exported into deterministic streams with explicit handling for unsupported operations or metadata classes.","acceptance_criteria":"Closure requires: deterministic stream emission tests, integration coverage over representative snapshots, and structured diagnostics for omitted or rejected operations.","notes":"Do not call this complete until the produced stream format is stable enough for the receive bead to consume under tests.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-03-23T01:06:26.762330403Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-23T06:11:30.220125788Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["btrfs","implementation","send-receive"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-nzv3.15","depends_on_id":"bd-nzv3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-23T01:06:26.762330403Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-nzv3.15","depends_on_id":"bd-nzv3.14","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-23T06:11:30.219190839Z","created_by":"PearlFox","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
-{"id":"bd-nzv3.16","title":"btrfs send/receive: implement receive apply path, roundtrip tests, and e2e logging","description":"Implement receive-side apply semantics for the scoped protocol and verify the user workflow end-to-end. This bead turns send/receive into an actual parity feature rather than a one-way export primitive.","acceptance_criteria":"Closure requires: deterministic receive tests, send→receive roundtrip coverage, explicit rejection tests for unsupported stream content, and at least one detailed e2e script that logs stream generation, apply, and verification results.","notes":"Parity/docs updates must say exactly what stream features and filesystem mutations are supported after closure.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-23T01:06:27.925148046Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-23T06:11:31.411780798Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["btrfs","send-receive","tests"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-nzv3.16","depends_on_id":"bd-nzv3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-23T01:06:27.925148046Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-nzv3.16","depends_on_id":"bd-nzv3.15","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-23T06:11:31.410713157Z","created_by":"PearlFox","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
-{"id":"bd-nzv3.17","title":"btrfs tree-log replay: extract replay semantics and recovery design","description":"Map the btrfs tree-log replay contract onto the current recovery architecture: when replay is attempted, ordering constraints, conflict rules, corruption handling, and interaction with normal mount/open flow.","acceptance_criteria":"Closure requires: implementation-ready design, scenario matrix for clean replay vs skip vs hard failure, and spec/parity updates that define the first supported replay envelope.","notes":"This bead must also define observability: replay attempted, replay skipped, replay failed, and replay completed should all have clear log/diagnostic surfaces.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-23T01:06:29.055966411Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-23T06:11:03.796993336Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["btrfs","replay","spec","tree-log"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-nzv3.17","depends_on_id":"bd-nzv3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-23T01:06:29.055966411Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
-{"id":"bd-nzv3.18","title":"btrfs tree-log replay: implement replay, crash coverage, and observability tests","description":"Implement the scoped tree-log replay path and prove it under crash-style scenarios with detailed observability checks. The feature is incomplete unless replay decisions are both correct and inspectable.","acceptance_criteria":"Closure requires: replay logic in the recovery path, deterministic unit/integration tests for replay primitives and crash envelopes, at least one end-to-end validation flow or harness scenario with detailed logging, and parity/docs updates.","notes":"Do not close on happy-path recovery alone; skip/fallback/corruption behavior is part of the acceptance surface.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"feature","created_at":"2026-03-23T01:06:30.142640954Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-23T06:11:32.624720077Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["btrfs","implementation","replay","tree-log"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-nzv3.18","depends_on_id":"bd-nzv3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-23T01:06:30.142640954Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-nzv3.18","depends_on_id":"bd-nzv3.17","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-23T06:11:32.623782362Z","created_by":"PearlFox","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
-{"id":"bd-nzv3.19","title":"Fix flaky btrfs log contract tests via deterministic capture design","description":"Remove the remaining race-prone tracing-subscriber behavior in the btrfs log-contract tests by redesigning capture to be deterministic under parallel test execution. The goal is to make the tests reliable without global serialization crutches.","acceptance_criteria":"Closure requires: a root-cause explanation, deterministic test harness behavior under repeated runs, explicit coverage for the previously flaky cases, and logging assertions that remain stable under parallel execution.","notes":"This bead should improve the harness design, not merely hide the race with broad test serialization.","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-03-23T01:06:31.278080685Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-23T06:11:04.131058050Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"labels":["btrfs","tests","tracing"],"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-nzv3.19","depends_on_id":"bd-nzv3","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-23T01:06:31.278080685Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}]}
